21/02/2008
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal on Wednesday (February 20th) allowed the provisional release of six former Croatian military commanders.
Jadranko Prlic, Bruno Stojic, Slobodan Praljak, Milivoj Petkovic,Valentin Coric and Berislav Pusic will be freed until May 4th, but must return for a few specific appearances in March and April.
All of them held senior posts in the self-proclaimed "Croatian Republic of Herzeg Bosna", which was terminated with the initialling of the Dayton Peace Accord.
The defendants are charged in connection with the murder, torture, and the persecution of Muslims southeast Bosnia and Herzegovina.
(ITAR-TASS, UN website, HRT - 20/02/08)
